Notebook[{

Cell[CellGroupData[{
Cell["\<\
Chapter 8: Advanced Techniques and Wolfram Language Integration\
\>", "Title",ExpressionUUID->"b1cd36ad-3753-804f-846e-d3a280f5dc9e"],

Cell["\<\
This chapter demonstrates sophisticated workflows that combine the \
server-side processing power of Google Earth Engine with the analytical, \
visualization, and machine learning capabilities of the Wolfram Language. \
Each section builds on the fundamentals covered in earlier chapters to show \
what becomes possible when these two platforms work together.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"4017d0ad-e8d0-9446-bc91-96e896852ec8"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Prerequisite:",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 " Authenticate per Section 1.3 and load the paclet with ",
 Cell["Needs[\"GoogleEarthEngineClient`\"]", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "83d11f65-d8e8-e649-b96b-b09831d6e80a"],
 "."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"a04c4a91-3332-0549-97f0-b7a14666e0ae"],

Cell["", "Text",
 CellFrame->{{0, 0}, {0, 
  1}},ExpressionUUID->"d5ccf6f5-54d1-564a-a376-b3ad39aca5a6"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["8.1 Machine Learning with GEE Data", "Chapter",ExpressionUUID->"0505bfe7-ada2-1242-855c-b75cf618f560"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The Wolfram Language provides a complete machine learning stack through ",
 Cell["Classify", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "6560dab0-2cf0-0344-af3f-e7fa28a9cfbf"],
 ", ",
 Cell["Predict", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "b63cb4e7-e4b9-e340-b415-40370e113216"],
 ", ",
 Cell["FindClusters", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "c59bff32-6cde-1e40-8711-cd846bf0b2a2"],
 ", and related functions. By extracting spectral data from GEE and feeding \
it into these built-in learners, you can build land cover classifiers, \
biomass predictors, and unsupervised clustering models without leaving a \
single notebook."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"36354628-9a55-a44d-b707-3477bafac886"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Supervised Classification: Land Cover from Sentinel-2", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"0959253b-5859-5d43-a3db-2c84cc763a3c"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The general workflow is: define training points with known labels, extract \
multi-band spectral values at those points using ",
 Cell["GEEGetSamples", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "ca93836a-a26a-104e-9832-cdc1fbdd222f"],
 ", train a classifier, and evaluate its performance. For an application of \
this workflow to crop-type classification specifically, see Section 5.3.2."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"3ee43115-6c3b-3f48-94d8-7438caac55aa"],

Cell[TextData[StyleBox["Step 1: Define training locations and labels.",
 FontWeight->Bold]], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"b9033c78-4c48-c249-a737-\
5d68e283e627"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Each training point is a ",
 Cell["GeoPosition", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "1492e288-16e5-a547-ae01-da61c9af199b"],
 " with a known land cover class. In practice you would derive these from \
field surveys, existing land cover maps, or careful visual interpretation."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"8ceae1e0-4182-3646-9531-ddbdcae2c90f"],

